{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Ground ramp services orchestrator - wheels chocks, ACU, GPU",
        "tags": ["ramp", "ground"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1 and the wheels chocks are ready. The B747 aircraft's engines are stopped. Install wheels chocks.", 
            "Flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1 and the acu is ready. The B747 aircraft's engines are stopped and wheels chocks have been installed. Connect acu.", 
            "Flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1 and the gpu is ready. The B747 aircraft's engines are stopped and wheels chocks have been installed. Connect gpu.", 
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-5.4-mini",
    },
    "max_iterations": 50000,
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200,
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at the San Francisco International Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """ 
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "ground_rampservices",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I perform ALL ground ramp services during aircraft turnaround, including
wheels chocks installation, ACU (air conditioning unit) connection, and
GPU (ground power unit) connection.
I am ALWAYS relevant for ANY of the following instructions:
  "Execute ground ramp services", "Perform ground ramp services",
  "Run ground ramp services", "Install wheels chocks", "Connect ACU",
  "Connect GPU", or any variation of the above.
I never refuse based on missing or null status fields — those are inputs
I retrieve, not prerequisites for my relevance.
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Flight number of the incoming aircraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },                 
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Gate id assigned to the aircraft."
                        },   
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Current flight status."
                        },
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Engines stop status."
                        },
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."
                        },
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "ACU readiness status."
                        },
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "GPU readiness status."
                        },
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Wheelchocks installation status."
                        },   
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "ACU connection status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "GPU connection status."
                        },   
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","gate_id"] 
                },
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of performing ground ramp services:
  - wheels chocks installation
  - ACU (air conditioning unit) connection
  - GPU (ground power unit) connection

CONTEXT DETECTION:
If the inquiry or the provided parameters indicate that this is a full ramp
services request (all three of wheels_chocks_readiness_status, acu_readiness_status,
and gpu_readiness_status are provided, or the instruction says "execute ground ramp
services" or similar), execute the FULL SEQUENCE below.

If the inquiry is for a single specific task only, execute only that task.

FULL SEQUENCE (execute in this exact order, waiting after each step):
CRITICAL: Execute ALL three steps unconditionally. Status fields in args
will be null — this is expected and normal. Each step produces the status
the next step conceptually depends on. Do NOT check or validate prior step
completion before calling the next sub-agent. Do NOT stop between steps.

STEP 1 - Wheels Chocks Installation
  a. Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_wheels chocks_install with:
       aircraft_type, gate_id, flight_status, engines_stop_status,
       wheels_chocks_readiness_status.
  b. Wait for response and store wheels_chocks_installation_status.
  c. Call TrackerAPI and log wheels_chocks_installation_status.
  d. Proceed immediately to STEP 2 regardless of wheels_chocks_installation_status value.

STEP 2 - ACU Connection
  a. Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_acu_connect with:
       aircraft_type, gate_id, flight_status, engines_stop_status,
       wheels_chocks_installation_status, acu_readiness_status.
  b. Wait for response and store acu_connection_status.
  c. Call TrackerAPI and log acu_connection_status.
  d. Proceed immediately to STEP 3 regardless of acu_connection_status value.

STEP 3 - GPU Connection
  a. Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_gpu_connect with:
       aircraft_type, gate_id, flight_status, engines_stop_status,
       wheels_chocks_installation_status, gpu_readiness_status.
  b. Wait for response and store gpu_connection_status.
  c. Call TrackerAPI and log gpu_connection_status.
  d. Proceed to RETURN SUMMARY.

After all three steps complete, provide the ramp services summary:
  ***************************************
  * Ground ramp services summary        *
  ***************************************
  ** flight number                  **: [flight_number]
  ** aircraft type                  **: [aircraft_type]
  ** gate id                        **: [gate_id]
  ** wheels chocks installation status**: [wheels_chocks_installation_status]
  ** acu connection status          **: [acu_connection_status]
  ** gpu connection status          **: [gpu_connection_status]

SINGLE-TASK DISPATCH (if only one task is requested):
  - If the inquiry is ONLY about wheels chocks installation:
      Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_install, wait,
      store and report wheels_chocks_installation_status.
  - If the inquiry is ONLY about ACU connection:
      Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_acu_connect, wait,
      store and report acu_connection_status.
  - If the inquiry is ONLY about GPU connection:
      Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_gpu_connect, wait,
      store and report gpu_connection_status.
  - If the inquiry is about none of the above, reply that you are not relevant.
            """ ${aaosa_instructions},  

            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": true,
                        "acu_connection_status": true,
                        "gpu_connection_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": true,
                        "acu_readiness_status": true,
                        "gpu_readiness_status": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": true,
                        "acu_connection_status": true,
                        "gpu_connection_status": true,
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools": [
                "TrackerAPI",
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_acu_connect",
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_gpu_connect",  
                "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_ground_wheels_chocks_install", 
            ]
        },

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {
                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
                """,
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Flight number."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Aircraft type."
                        },         
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Gate id."
                        },     
                        "wheels_chocks_installation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Wheelchocks installation status."
                        },   
                        "gpu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "GPU connection status."
                        },      
                        "acu_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "ACU connection status."
                        },      
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Wheelchocks readiness status."
                        },
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "ACU readiness status."
                        },
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "GPU readiness status."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_ground_rampservices.aircraft_ground_rampservices.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
